# Git & Version Control

## Commit Guidelines

- Use conventional commits with git flow conventions.
- Format: `type(scope): description`
- Examples:
  - `feat(auth): add Google login with Supabase`
  - `fix(users): correct user profile data fetching`
  - `refactor(components): simplify hero section layout`
  - `docs(readme): update installation instructions`

## Pull Request Guidelines

- Write clear, descriptive PR titles and descriptions.
- Reference related issues or tasks in PRs.
- Ensure all tests pass before requesting review.
- Fix all lint and type errors before merging code.
